			this.buffer = [];

			}

		 * Push a value onto the end
		 * @param channel number
		 * @param value number
		 */
		push(channel, value) {
			this.writeHead[channel] += 1;
			if (this.writeHead[channel] > this.size) {
				this.writeHead[channel] = 0;
			}
			this.buffer[channel][this.writeHead[channel]] = value;

		 * Get the recorded value of the channel given the delay
		 * @param channel number
		 * @param delay number delay samples
		 */
		get(channel, delay) {
			let readHead = this.writeHead[channel] - Math.floor(delay);

				readHead += this.size;
			}
			return this.buffer[channel][readHead];
		}
	}

`,(0,ft.jsx)(e.p,{children:`When a physical object vibrates, its harmonic overtones will all sound at once, at different amplitudes.

The relation of the different harmonics is called timbre.
It gives any instrument its unique character.

The sum of all sinewave partials will produce a more complex waveform.`}),`
